# Codex rewrites machine-managed state (marketplace timestamps/revisions, hook
# trust hashes) into these files on nearly every launch. The `codex-config` clean
# filter normalizes that churn out of the committed blob so they stay stable
# across launches and machines. Install the filter with `just git-filters`
# (it is local git config, not carried by these attributes alone).
# Filter script: ~/scripts/mask-codex-state.sh
.codex/config.toml filter=codex-config
.codex/*.config.toml filter=codex-config
